default3.1.default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultLike other industry members, 
defaultTalkTalk
default takes a zero tolerance approach to illegal child abuse images online. Currently our efforts are focused on helping prevention. We are a longstanding member of the Internet Watch Foundation and pay the maximum membership fee. This summer we, along with the other ISPs, committed to a further £1m of funding for the IWF to continue its work in identifying illegal child abuse images on the internet. 
defaultTalkTalk
default also chaired the working group that supported the membership review of the IWF which has led to their move to proactively seeking out illegal child abuse images online in addition to following public reports.  
default3.2.default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultWe automatically download the block list of known websites containing illegal images from the IWF on a 
defaultdaily
default basis, and apply it to our filtering system, which means that every customer is blocked from accessing those websites across the whole network. 
default3.3.default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultCustomers who try and access these websites are presented with a splash page informing them the content is blocked because it has been found to be illegal by the IWF. In the summer, a group comprising the IWF, CEOP and Lucy Faithful Foundation, a charity who work with offenders, agreed a new stronger set of wording that 
defaultTalkTalk
default implemented in August, along with the other three major ISPs. The wording is: 
defaultAccess has been denied by your internet access provider because this page may contain indecent images of children as identified by the Internet Watch Foundation.
defaultDeliberate attempts to access this or related material may result in you committing a criminal offence.
defaultThe consequences of deliberately accessing such material are likely to be serious. People arrested risk losing their family and friends, access to children (including their own) and their jobs.
