defaultbelive
default the issue of extremist material and material intended to promote 
defaultterroism
default or acts of violence is 
defaultpredominatly
default a matter for law 
defaultenforcment
default agencies and should be addressed via a joined up, multi-pronged approach to tackling extremism and 
defaultterroism
default. As an ISP we adhere to requests to remove content that has been found to be illegal under current UK legislation. This may include material found to be 
defaultextremist
default or material intended to promote 
defaultterroism
default or acts of violence. We are also in the process of 
defaultfinalising
default an agreement with the Home Office to include their filtering list of known 
defaultterroist
default websites that breach Terrorism Act 2006 but that the policing Counter Terrorism Internet Referral Unit have been unable to get taken down, for example because they are hosted abroad. We intend to add this into our ‘weapons and violence’ category within 
defaultHomeSafe
default, so that our customers can choose to filter access if they want. 
